          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Advanced Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Hadoken</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/magination/gfx/star3.gif" width="21" height="22" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size=1>(4.40)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=25687">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=12438">JD "Bog Wraith" Duncan</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=12438&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> My take on a semi-creatureless Cald deck based on some ideas from both Cald Spell and Amplified Boom.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> September 21, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Magi: <br>
Good ol&#39; <a href="javascript:card_browser(375)">Ash<a href="javascript:card_browser(377)">Gar</a></a> <br>
(Starting: Depends on the game play)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(376)">Barak</a><br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a>)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(676)">Amanax</a> <br>
(Starting: <a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a>)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Creatures<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(359)">Arbolit</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(476)">Ormagon</a> x1<br>
Inferno <a href="javascript:card_browser(337)">Xyx</a> x2<br>
<br>
<br>
Relics<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(386)">Scroll of Fire</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(546)">Gorgle&#39;s Glasses</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(678)">Abraxin&#39;s Crown</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(383)">Heat Lens</a> x3<br>
Boomstick x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(652)">Rayje&#39;s Belt</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(787)">Rayje&#39;s Sword</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(509)">Robe of the Ages</a> x1<br>
<br>
<br>
Spells<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(498)">Thunderquake</a> x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(357)">Storm Cloud</a> x3<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(392)">Syphon Vortex</a> x3 <br>
Crushing Heat x3<br>
Spirit Drain x2<br>
Brushfire x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(390)">Flame Geyser</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(550)">Wildfire</a> x1<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(790)">Beam of Light</a> x2<br>
Sandswirl x1<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
TOTAL : 40 Cards <br>
<br>
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Ok well here we go!<br>
<br>
If you get a choice, go second.  This will allow you to see what you are going up against.  Like I mentioned above Good ol&#39; Ashgar&#39;s starting cards will vary depending on what your opponent plays on their first turn.  If you need protection from Hubdra&#39;s Spear or T&#39;lok and other things that affect you if you have no creatures then grab the Arbolit.  If your opponent has a ton of wee ones in play then grab the Flame Geyser and have some fun.  Similarly if they have a few big creatures then grab the Boomstick.  Good ol&#39; Ashgar is also great because they know that basically whatever they attack with will die due to Combat Reflexes.  The versatility of Good ol&#39; Ashgar is the main reason that I run him first.<br>
<br>
Barak is up next.  Grab the Arbolit and use prophecy.  Hopefully by now you have drawn an Abraxin&#39;s Crown, otherwise play a Gorgle&#39;s Glasses and kill off some creatures to draw a lot of cards.  You should be able to just play it out and kill a Magi or two with Barak.<br>
<br>
Now here is my favorite Magi.  Grab the Syphon Vortex and use it on the biggest creatue in play.  This should net you some serious energy.  Whats that they have alot of little ones and nothing worth Syphoning, dont worry, throw down a Flame Geyser or Wildfire and net a huge amount of energy with Pyromaniac.  Even though his energize rate kinda sucks he makes up for this by playing a free Brushfire every turn and even gaining an energy if used with a Scroll of Fire.  Amanax should easily be a flip-kill otherwise he&#39;ll cleen up pretty quick anyways.<br>
<br>
Now on to specific card strategy:<br>
<br>
Ormagon is great.  He allows you to reset things if they get really bad and offers some massive protection if needed.<br>
<br>
Inferno Xyx is my favorite card in the deck.  Just imagine a really big Boomstick, now imagine a really big Boomstick with an Abraxin&#39;s Crown.  Nuff said.<br>
<br>
Heat Lens is great for getting rid of those pesky cards that could screw you over later in the game.<br>
<br>
Rayje&#39;s Belt and Rayje&#39;s Sword are specifically for getting rid of burrow. The other plus is that Rayje&#39;s Belt is re-usable.<br>
<br>
Storm Cloud is great against both Magi and creatures espacially with a Scroll of Fire in play.<br>
<br>
Crushing Heat not only gets rid of creatures, but it also locks down everything on their side for a turn, Hehehe.<br>
<br>
Spirit Drain is a useful way to get energy off of Magi especially if you haven&#39;t gotten an Abraxin&#39;s Crown yet.<br>
<br>
Beams are for those pesky critters who just wont die, and also for those annoying relics.<br>
<br>
And finally Sandswirl.  Probably one of the best cards around.  Think about it, an X turn Rayje&#39;s Belt that doesn&#39;t stop like Rayje&#39;s Belt does if it get discarded from play, what could be better?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you for reading this and I look forward to hearing some feed back. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magination/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=25687"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25687" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magination/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></td></tr></table></td>
        </tr>
